A/O: Welcome to the office of the Richmond county Clerk. Our business hours are 9-5 Monday
through Friday, please listen closely to our menu options. For land records including deeds,
mortgages and real state matters, please press one. For court related matters including
licensing ser...

help you?

lot? That didn't come up?

Richmondcountyclerk.com?

JAMELIA: What's the last name that it will be under?
DINO: K-O-S-I-C
JAMELIA: First name?
DINO: C-E-M-A-L
[PAUSE] [Music playing in the background]
JAMELIA: What was the address to the property you were looking for?
DINO: 739 Post avenue. It's weird, it's like one of these old houses on West branch, so there
is like three addresses on one lot.
JAMELIA: You purchased it back in the 80's?
DINO: Yeah. 737, 739, 741.
JAMELIA: Yes, I see it here it's with the CEMAL and REVIJA [Phonetic]?
DINO: Um, yeah.
JAMELIA: Yeah, it's here.
DINO: Okay, um.. Can I come... I can come pick it up correct?
JAMELIA: Yeah, you can come anytime, you are going to come to 130 Stuyvesant
[Phonetic] on the 2nd floor.
DINO: Okay.
JAMELIA: And as soon as you walk in, there is going to be counter right in front of
you. You are going to go there and give the gentleman your information, and they will pull it up for
you and they will print it out. You just need a regular copy right? Or certified?
DINO: Um.. if I need certified, what type of information do I need?
JAMELIA: Certified, it's 4 dollars for page. Cash. for the certified copy and it's 25
cents a page per regular copy.
DINO: Okay, about how many pages is that?
JAMELIA: 5
DINO: Okay. And that's it right?
JAMELIA: And that's it yeah.
DINO: And you are open until 5:00 today correct?
JAMELIA: Correct.
DINO: Okay, alright, thank you.
JAMELIA: You're welcome.
DINO: See you, have a good day.
JAMELIA: Thanks.
[End of Call]

DINO: Yeah.

DINO: Yeah I did, I went a couple days ago bro.

Body:
JORGE [ID'd on session 575] to MEDIN a/k/a DINO
JORGE: Yo bro. What's up?
DINO: What's bro?
JORGE: Why you don't answer my phone man?
DINO: I was sleeping.
JORGE: You're still sleeping at this time?
DINO: I'm not sleeping now, that's why I answered.
JORGE: Oh.
DINO: You alright? My father said you came over there today.
JORGE: What's going on?
DINO: I have to have the sectional inspection coming in a couple of days.
JORGE: So when are you gonna do the railings?
DINO: I go get them tomorrow.
JORGE: C'mon, I don't want to spend to much money there and I don't want to waste my time
there. You know.
DINO: What do you mean?
JORGE: I mean, I already did all my work there, so I gotta get paid.
DINO: Most of it, yeah. You did most of it, yeah.
JORGE: You know?
DINO: Yeah, I hear you, I understand that bro. I'm not... Bro, you act like I'm not gonna give
you the money.
JORGE: It's not the point.
DINO: I know you need it.
JORGE: I told you, you wanted finish and then get out of there.
DINO: Yes.
JORGE: I want to get that out of my head, this way. I don't wanna leave you like... I'm not like
Frankie, you know?
DINO: I know that.
JORGE: Get the money and out of there. C'mon.
DINO: I know that, I know that.
JORGE: Alright? Please.
DINO: Yes.
JORGE: Work it out and get us out of here
DINO: I can [Stammers] get the kitchen cabinets for upstairs, I can get the counter top, the
faucet and the railings. I can get them all tomorrow.
JORGE: Okay, alright. Work it, get it done, let's get paid. Let's get all happy that's what I want to
hear.
DINO: Yes.
JORGE: You call me back, I come back. Whatever you wanna do with me so..
DINO: Okay.
JORGE: But I want to straighten this out okay?
DINO: Yeah, I hear you dude 'cause I want to straighten it out too. You think I don't want to
straighten it out too? Believe me I want to straighten it out.
JORGE: Okay?
DINO: Alright.
JORGE: Alright DINO call me tomorrow. You got my picture? I sent you pictures, how to look
like.
DINO: Yes, yes Sir.
JORGE: Alright.
DINO: Alright, good night.
[End of Call]

Body:
Automated Operator Recording: Hello, this is a free call from an inmate at New York City
department to correction.
UM9015 to DINO
DINO and UM9015 engage in a conversation regarding DINO'S father doing better and going to
therapy.
UM9015 asks DINO about the baby and DINO says the baby is fine.
UM9015: How are you doing? Are you staying healthy or your smoking or eating bad?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Yeah, I'm smoking a little bit but I'm being.... active everyday.
UM9015: Alright, be careful kid.
DINO: Yeah, I know.
[Voices Overlap]
UM9015: I put my weight back on. I'm back up to 245.
DINO: Really?
UM9015: Yeah.
DINO: Alright. Are you feeling alright?
UM9015: I'm not sick anymore. My body is finally back to normal. I'm going to the bathroom
regularly. I'm eating normally. Uhm... but now I gotta watch the diabetes. But even that, the sugar
level coming down. I was in the high 2s, low 3s, every time they measured me. Every time they
took a glucose test and now I'm like in the low 2s or high 1s. It's getting a little better. And my
back pain is not there no more. My body is done from that shit. It took an awful long time.
DINO: You feel healthy?
UM9015: Healthier, yeah. I still feel like a fat slob. But... I don't feel uh... I sleep better. I close
eyes, I go to sleep, I fall asleep right away. Like a normal human being, instead of being a jerk
off.
DINO: You spoke to Athena [Phonetic] ?
UM9015: No, as a matter a fact I haven't spoken to her in almost 2 weeks. I have to give her a
call. I'll call her later.
DINO tells UM9015 he spoke to TINA MARIE a couple of days ago and she sent UM9015 the
message to call.
UM9015: What is going on? [Unintelligible] that thing?
DINO: Fucking terrible.
UM9015: Things are terrible on my end too.
DINO: I know, cuzz.
UM9015: I'm talking 4 and 2.
[Minimization Start - 12:53:02 Minimization End- 12:54:03]
UM9015: Who is friend sleeps 2 beds away from me and knows about him. Copped out to 4
and 3. He just came home from another bid 2 years ago, a year and a half ago. He got four and
three for the same thing I got in trouble for. You know? He's a predicate and he got that. Me, I'm
not a predicate. My last felony was 27 years ago, that doesn't even count.
DINO: Oh, they didn't bring it up in court?
UM9015: Oh, they did bring up in the beginning, in the arrangement and the first 2 times there
was a trial when what's his name was there? when Lance was actually there, they were bringing
up when they were still doing the bail stuff. They were making me out to sound like John Gotti or
something.
DINO: Ridiculous.
UM9015: As far as I'm reading here and hearing from here, you know, felonies after 10 years g
away. So I imagine for almost 30 years, they should go away too.
DINO: I guess depending on what it is.
UM9015: It was a conviction of an E Felony not even like...
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: I'm pretty sure it was you were fucking a kid back then, it wasn't that
serious.
UM9015: I was 20 years old when I got convicted, [stammers] even when I got convicted, I stil
wasn't 20 years old yet. It was in February when I got convicted of 1991. I got arrested in January
of 1990... but on that one I made bail. The bail was nothing, like 2 -3,000 thousand back then.
DINO: I got a question for you, you know the GMC terrains, they are like Mini
Delani's.
UM9015: It looks like the Envoy. It's like the X3 to the X5.
DINO: Yes. Did you ever recognize one of those or come across one of those?
Ever encounter with the...
[Voices Overlap]
UM9015: No, no. He only had a... it was a Chrysler 200 like a charcoal gray.
DINO: Okay.
UM9015: Check this out. Remember I told you that the kid that was next to me, that Lance was
representing, that copped out to 4 and 3, same guy. Echo [Phonetic]. Same guy. That was his
name, he described him, the car, everything, and it was in the same area but just in the lower
street numbers, like 40-50s-60s. Same guy. This guy is cleaning up, doing the whole
neighborhood.
DINO: I don't know. I tried to tell you dude.
UM9015: I know. It was too late, even after the first time it was done. But he kept it going for a
long time. How long did it go on for? Do you remember? 6 months, 7 months?
DINO: Yeah I would say about that.
UM9015: I think it was from like October, November, up until April so... Hold on, November,
December, January, February, March, April. 6 months, that sounds about right.
DINO: Yeah but how many times? Like 7, 8 times?
UM9015: Oh more than that, on my paper work they got me down on 14 counts.
DINO: Oh wow.
UM9015: So I am thinking that's 14 times and that's every 2, 3 weeks, every 3 weeks he woul
come. You know? With the story that he is coming from upstate or whatever the hell, blah, blah,
blah. Ah man...
DINO: How you holding up in there? Fucking nightmare no?
UM9015: Trying to get used to it which is fucked up but I wanna get out of here really, I wanna
upstate. [Unintelligible] I gotta go. I wanna get it over with already. Why wasting my time here
though, the worst it is, I wish I can get up there and start my program to start putting in the time to
that this way I can earn my [Unintelligible] and you know? Good time and stuff, and maybe get
the hell out of there cause Peter told me that he saw [Unintelligible] other day in the a... And he
told him that even if I do the full that I should be home in about year and half or so.
[Minimization start: 12:58:56- Minimization end: 12:59:56]
UM9015 and DINO continue conversation about how DINO feels terrible.
[Minimization start: 13:00:32- Minimization end: 13:01:34]
DINO asks UM9015 if he has food in there.
[Minimization start: 13:02:06- Minimization end: 13:02:51]
[End of Call]
MB: EF

Body:
[Words / Conversation in ITALICS are spoken in ALBANIAN]
UM7515/1237/5875/8642 TO DINO
UM5875: Hey, you?
DINO: Yo.
UM5875: How are you man?
DINO: What you doing?
UM5875: Nothing, you?
DINO: What's going on?
UM5875: Nothing, about to walk into my house in a couple of minutes. Fucking freezing cuz.
DINO: You want to meet me?
UM5875: What?
DINO: You want to meet me?
UM5875: Yeah. I love to see you.
DINO: Why didn't you call me?
UM5875: What do you mean cuzz? I have, have told you cuzz. I told you that last night.
DINO: Do I have to come over there?
UM5875: Huh?
DINO: To come there?
UM5875: Uh....Where are you now?
DINO: With my friend here in Hylan.
UM5875: Oh yeah? How did you get around today?
DINO: By taxi.
UM5875: Why didn't you call me?
DINO: I did, Jen said she needed the car.
UM5875: What do you mean?
DINO: She said she needed the car at 3:00, cuz. She had a doctor's appointment
and some shit.
UM5875: Why didn't you call me cuz? Why did you call her, you should have called me cuzz.
DINO: I did call your phone and she picked up.
UM5875: You should have called. Make sure you get in touch with me cuz. Hear me voice cuz
DINO: Alright, it's not big deal.
UM5875: No, I'm saying. Make sure you talk to me cuz because I ended up taking her to the
doctors. [Audio Glitch] I ended up taking her to the doctor.
DINO: Do you want me [Unintelligible] talk?
UM5875: Huh?
DINO: What?
[Audio Glitch]
UM5875: Yeah, why not. I guess.
DINO: Hold on. I'm not gonna force you to do something you don't want to do.
UM5875: No cause, it doesn't really matter cuz. I had to see my friend cuzz, but I don't care, I
can see you. It doesn't matter.
DINO: Alright.
UM5875: At then end of the day he's done with all of them.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Yeah, I got you.
UM5875: I'm a fat bastard. I eat ice cream like crazy my nigga.
DINO: Alright, I'm calling a cab right now.
UM5875: Why are you calling a cab for?
DINO: I'm a little stacked.
[Audio Glitch]
UM5875: Oh.
DINO: Unless you want to take me straight home.
UM5875: Huh?
DINO: Can you take me straight home?
UM5875: Yeah, I can take you straight home.
DINO: Alright, so come get me.
UM5875: Alright, so get me a second. Go to my house real quick.
DINO: Alright, what are you looking at 40 minutes?
UM5875: Not even cuz, no.
DINO: Okay, bye.
[End of Call]

Body:
UM7515/5875 to MEDIN KOSIC a/k/a DINO
UM7515/5875: I'll be right there, cuz.
DINO: Yeah, it's a'right. 'Cause I don't have to go now.
UM7515/5875: Why? I left the girl right there.
DINO: Huh?
UM7515/5875: The girl is in front of your house. Why don't you have to go?
DINO: 'Cause this fucking kid is a motherfucker. That's why.
UM7515/5875: Come on, cuz! I just stopped whatever I was doing for you cuzzie.
DINO: Yeah, I know that.
UM7515/5875: I swear to my mother I just did mad shit for you cuz.
DINO: I know. I just dead him [Pause].
[Voices Overlap]
UM7515/5875: Call that scumbag and tell him that's not happening right now cuz [Pause].
So, we can't do shit like that cuz.
DINO: Yes. He asked me to fucking go Tottenville, and go see the kid.
UM7515/5875: So, what?
DINO: To go to Tottenville, to meet the kid in Tottenville.
UM7515/5875: Whatever cuz. I stopped doing what I had to do cuz. I don't give a fuck.
DINO: I...
UM7515/5875: Is this because of me cuz? [Stutters] You...
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: It's not because of you, it's not because of you.
UM7515/5875: A'right 'cause I'm ready cuz, I don't care. Whatever it is.
DINO: It's not because of you, it's not because of you.
UM7515/5875: So, what happened?
DINO: It's not because of you [Pause]. He's a fucking idiot, that's what it
is.
UM7515/5875: So, it's dead.
DINO: Sits there and calls me 10:30, 11:00 o'clock last night. 'Yo
please got people, blah, blah, blah.' A'right I fucking stayed here, fucking stay here [Pause] . I
fucking [Pause] Try to stop the bus from fuckin moving and now, 'Oh, you know what? Forget it
until the morning.
UM7515/5875: Why? Because we were late or [Pause]?
DINO: Just forget it cuz. I'm sorry. I'm very sorry [Pause]. I'll make it up to
you.
UM7515/5875: You don't have to make it up for me. Just show up right there, I'll be right
there. Call this kid see...
[End of Call]

Body:
DINO to UF (Using TINA MARIE's phone)
They greet. DINO asks her how she has been. UF says that she is okay, especially because her
BMW car is broken, the engine fall out. DINO tells UF that he can't believe it. UF says that they
just did all that work in the front of the car for nothing. UF confirms with DINO that the engine
literally fell out of the car.
UF: The Chevy hasn't sold, whatever. Chris's family, driving me crazy. Uhm, now
they text me through his cousin Maria. Because, yeah 'cause obviously his aunt and his mother
don't [Unintelligible]. And now his mother's like 'Oh, Tin Mari. I hardly understand what you say to
me. Uh, please just talk to Maria. Maria will, will make me understand'. And Chris is going, just
laughs. He's like, 'She's so full of shit'. I'm like, 'I know'. So, you know I have to do everything
through you know, have it all... niece. Not her mouth piece.
DINO: [Chuckles]
UF: Uhm... it's ridiculous, it's ridiculous. I call them now 'The three ladies'. I'm
like, 'cause they're really like...
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Yeah, like... like they...
[Voices overlap]
UF: They're old. That's what they are. They're old ladies...
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Like 'The three wise men' [Chuckles].
UF: [Unintelligible]. They're old school, old [Audio fades] European ladies.
[Stutters] That's the problem. Huh...
DINO: I can't believe that engine dropped outta that car.
UF: Me neither. After we just did all that work to the front ends.
DINO: I have the day...
[Voices overlap]
UF: The [Unintelligible], this, that, the other things. If we could of solve with this...
[Voices overlap]
DINO: You were driving it?
UF: It was... no. It was put up on the list. By not only you know our mechanic,
who fixed everything still. But by three other mechanics of people who looked at the car. And
every single one of them said, 'Oh, the whole front end is new. Oh, you know they did everything
new. Everything's new in the front end'. Plus the tires had all new routers, brakes. What a fucking
mat. What a fucking shame. What a shame.
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Where did it happen?
UF: I actually, I didn't have the car. Tina did. What a fucking shame. [Pause] And
now he's like 'This is why I don't wanna get involved'. And [Unintelligible], and you know look at
what happened'. And I'm like 'Oh my God'. He's like, 'I know you didn't know', he said. 'And I
know no body new', he said that...
[Voices overlap]
DINO: No body new. Wow.
UF: He said, 'I'm there...'
[Minimization start: 17:00:30 - Minimization end of call: 17:02:46]
[End of Call]
MB: MC
SB: TP

Participants: DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin MARIE, TINA
Body:
TINA MARIE to DINO
TINA MARIE: Hello.
DINO: Yeah.
TINA MARIE: Okay I told tell her I'll call her right back. She's [Unintelligible]
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: That's terrible, man.
TINA MARIE: I can't even think about it whatever. You know, it is what it is. Chris got
[phonetic] got sentenced did he tell you?
DINO: Did he?
TINA MARIE: Oh no I'm sorry. Chris goes for sentencing on October 3rd, sorry. He goes
for sentencing, he didn't get sentenced he goes.
DINO: He copped out.
TINA MARIE: I don't know what that means but I know...
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Meaning that he pleaded guilty to the charges and now they just
awaiting sentencing.
TINA MARIE: Right something four years.
DINO: Oh man.
TINA MARIE: So he goes sentencing October 3rd. So I'm done dealing with this
ridiculous freaking storage place. I'm so done with them and their nick and dime thieves and this
and that. So, I told them that, 'Listen, I can't get out there to pick up the key. And I said, 'To be
honest with you, the weekends are really better for me.' I said, 'Sunday is really the best day for
me. I was like, 'And you people weren't there.' He's like 'Do you want me to certify... send out
the key to you via mail?' I was like, 'Yes please can you please send it certified mail?'
[Unintelligible] I told him, [phonetic] 'Why didn't you tell that two fucking months ago?' So he's
doing that today and I told him [phonetic] I want everything out of that unit Dino [phonetic] before
the 25th, because on the 25th it's another $330 dollars. I don't have it anymore that's it I'm done. I
just want to go out there you know if you can use the futon, if you can use any other furniture
please take it but you know.
DINO and TINA engage in a social conversation regarding TINA needing a U-HAUL to move all
the stuff out because she has a lot of things.
DINO offers to drive the U-HAUL for TINA.
TINA: I just want to, you know, I just want to get rid of this stuff. If you can use it or
if you can keep some of it for Chris, that's fine. Otherwise, it's going in the garbage. I don't know
what else to do with it.
DINO: Alright, we'll go.
DINO and TINA engage in a social conversation regarding DINA trying to be nice and give
things away instead of selling it.
TINA offers a almost new futon to DINO. DINO agrees to look at the furniture.
DINO: I can't believe he's gonna be gone for this long man.
TINA MARIE: Well he [Chris] was on the phone with Athena [phonetic] yesterday then he
called me he was crying. I was like, 'What's the matter?' He said, 'Well I was crying on the
phone with Athena and I think she heard.' And I was like you can't do that you can't cry on the
phone with your daughter, you know she's 11.'
DINO: I know but by the time he comes home she's gonna 13.
TINA and DINO engage in a social conversation regarding ATHENA not calling her grandmother
nor Ann Marie.
TINA and DINO engage in a social conversation regarding ATHENA possibly getting a child
telephone to be able to be in touch with her.

Body:
DINO to TINA MARY
TINA MARY tells DINO that the new bill come to the 25th and they want everything out of there by
then (Storage) DINO asks TINA when she wants to go. TINA says that she is working but she is
off Saturday and Sunday. DINO tells HER that then they will go there Saturday. TINA agrees.
DINO says that he will stop by her later and he will drop her some money. TINA acknowledges
and thanks him.
TINA tells DINO that he is going to sentence on the third (Oct) and then they'll move him to a
different part of Rikers for three or four weeks and then they'll move him Upstate. TINA says that
she doesn't like the fact that they will move him to another part of Rikers for three weeks.
DINO tells her that it's nothing she can't do because they do whatever they want and they don't
take in consideration anybody's feeling or anything like that. TINA tells DINO that she is just worry
that he won't be in the drug program for three weeks.
TINA says that he is going upstate but he doesn't know where he is going. DINO says that he
probably will far like three hours away. TINA says that she doesn't know where those places are
at. DINO says that neither him.
TINA tells DINO that she told him (Chris) to take classes that benefit him not to take classes just
for taking anything, especially Auto-Mechanic, because he knows that when he comes home that
he is not physical fit and he is too old to get under a car.
DINO tells TINA that he doesn't want to think about it. TINA says that his daughter is going to
hight school and she is going to need her father. DINO tells TINA that him (Chris ) will be home
before she goes to hight school.
TINA says that she actually the little girl turned 12 and that 4 years in a long time. DINO asks
TINA if he has been there for 6 months already. TINA confirms.
TINA says that the girl was looking to come to TINA's because she doesn't like her living
arrangement because she can't stand living there. While she is there she constantly want to go
to her grandparents house. TINA continues talking about the little girl having nightmares and
waking up in the middle of the night, thinking that everyone is going to die. TINA continues
explaining DINO about the girl not liking her mom's new boyfriend. DINO says that he thought
that the mother was with this guy for a while. TINA says that with the first one not this one. DINO
asks TINA if the mother is switching boyfriends often. TINA says not all the time.
They continue talking about the girl's mom, Chris' ex, and about how the girl feels about it. SHE
continues talking about the same subject. TINA explains what's the kids arrangements between
the girl's mom and her boyfriend and his kids.
DINO says that this situation is going to turn out to be really bad. TINA agrees.
DINO says that he won't be home for at least two years. TINA concurs. DINO asks TINA what
she is going to do now. TINA says that she has no idea that she will try to figure it out. TINA says
that she is trying to get control of the finances because the bills are coming like the car
Insurance, and she is going to transfer the Chevy under her name, that she already took the

UM5875: Yes I coming over at your place.

We're getting closer.

DINO: A'ight

Participants: DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] DOLORES/MOTHER/FORMERLY UF4614 - ] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
ANTHONY [Using UF4614's number] to MEDIN a/k/a DINO
ANTHONY: Hello you hear me what happened?
DINO: Yeah...
ANTHONY: What happened?
DINO: They said call her Monday morning. I was like ' Yo dude what the fuck bro.'
I was like 'Nobody told me the 25th.' I was like there was no inspector here yesterday.' I was
like ' Nobody has access to it so how could he say the apartment's not ready.' I was like 'When I
called here they told me...' He said ' No we have it for the 20th. ' I said ' Dude they told me the
25th.
ANTHONY: Oh God. You gotta come by here later.
DINO: For what?
ANTHONY: 'Cause you have to [Unintelligible] me anyway and plus you gotta explain
this to them.
DINO: Explain what to them? There's nothing to explain to them.
ANTHONY: Listen they already moved my mother downstairs, understand? We're not
wanted here at all.
DINO: What do you want me to do?
ANTHONY: I want you to explain it to them.
DINO: There's not much explain, you can explain.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: [Unintelligible] asking ' Where's Dino, where's Dino?' Just come here and
show fucking face bro.
DINO: Show face for what? There's nothing to show face for. Like if I'm
[Unintelligible] or something.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Explain to them like you're like... my cousin, that's all. You gotta come see
me anyways what are you talking about bro? Explain it bro.
DINO: For what bro?
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Today's Thursday bro what do you mean for what?
DINO: Yeah it's not gonna work out today.
ANTHONY: Dino it has to work out today bro it has to...
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: It's not.
ANTHONY: What do you mean it's not, Dino. What do you mean it's not...
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: It's not...
ANTHONY: It's not D [phonetic] what do you mean it's not?
DINO: Nah I need a couple more days. [Unintelligible] you gotta wait a couple
more days.
ANTHONY: Dude what I gotta wait a couple more days for?
DINO: Because you gotta wait a couple more days.
ANTHONY: For what reason bro give me a good reason.
DINO: What the fuck once I start fucking paying bro it's gonna get fucking paid.
ANTHONY: Alright so come she me anyway bro you haven't come see me bro.
DINO: Relax what the fuck man.
ANTHONY: I lend your friend $100 yesterday. I lent your friend.
DINO: Where's all the fucking money I'm still waiting for. 'Yeah I'll pay you back, I'll
pay you back.' I'm still waiting on that too.
ANTHONY: [Unintelligible] $200 yesterday. What are you talking about you're not talking
about me bro, we talking about the money. And I'm going through this money bro. We have to go
shopping buy shit.
DINO: How are you going through that money? Doing what?
ANTHONY: Because bro I'm buying stuff... I'm going shopping..
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Oh
ANTHONY: I'm buying cigarettes what do you want me to do?
DINO: You shouldn't be spending more than 30, 40 bucks a day.
ANTHONY: Alright so that's still adding up bro.
DINO: You gonna run through that whole thing?
ANTHONY: No I'm not going to run through the whole thing that's why we have to go buy
the stuff we have to go buy everything.
DINO: So go buy it. I gotta take you?
ANTHONY: Well you could take me for some of it because I don't want them to know
I've had this money. I can [Unintelligible] refrigerator [phonetic] and like one another thing but
everything else I can't let them know.
DINO: They don't know that... he gave you that money?
ANTHONY: No.
DINO: Wow.
ANTHONY: [Unintelligible] what are you talking about? We were [Unintelligible] bro after
I gave it to you what are you talking about?
DINO: Yeah so what you're gonna get it back.
ANTHONY: I'm saying that's what's left, and that's not even left.
DINO: Oh my God
ANTHONY: That's why I have to get that shit as soon as possible. This is a nightmare D
this is no good. I can't tell mom this.
DINO: Can't tell her what? There's nothing to tell her.
ANTHONY: I can't let them know we [Unintelligible] later on bro.[Unintelligible]
DINO: There's nothing to tell her what is there to tell her.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: They like you over here bro jut come here and if they
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: [Mumbles] ahead of schedule, not my fault. Unless he's lying to me.
ANTHONY: You gotta put your number down or my number down as the landlord .
DINO: I did already. I did.
ANTHONY: You put yours?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: And how you gonna get [Unintelligible]
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Yeah don't worry about it. Unless he's lying to me.
ANTHONY: Your father might be lying bro. Your father maybe don't want to hear it bro he
don't want to be going to wake you up or nothing.
DINO: Nah.
ANTHONY: I don't know bro...
DINO: I don't know if I ask him is he gonna tell me yeah he's lying to you.
ANTHONY: But inspector is not going to lie bro. Why would inspector lie for bro? Come
one.. it's not like you know they doing everything that's what they.. they just go in and inspect. It's
not like they doing hard work. They not gonna drive all the way there and fucking you know what I
mean? Why would he lie? You put the banister [phonetic] up right?
DINO: No he's coming tomorrow to do it.
ANTHONY: That could be it right there.
DINO: No because he said the landlord said that it's not ready. The landlord
[Unintelligible]
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Alright so yeah that's your father..
DINO: I asked him bro he's not going to lie to me about that for what?
ANTHONY: I don't think the inspector would lie, for what reason?
DINO: But why would he lie? For what reason does he have to lie..
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: There's no reason to drive all the way to Staten Island when the place is in
the Bronx the head quarters.
DINO: I don't... I can't see him moving in no matter what dude, don't matter. So why
is he gonna
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Your father should just put the stuff in the basement, so he knows that
already.
DINO: Yeah that's what I'm saying.
ANTHONY: I don't man but this is not good I can't let her know .Paula [phonetic] knows
'cause I'm sleeping up here with Paula. And Paula.. I can't let mom know bro. Yesterday she was
crying.. she wants her own home bro.
DINO: Yeah I hear you dude. What you want me to do ? I'm trying my best over
here champ.
ANTHONY: Just come by later
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Like there's no pressure on me at all...
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: I know there is bro just come by later alright?
DINO: Like there's no fucking pressure on me.
ANTHONY: I know there's pressure on you bro.
DINO: Yeah what give me another fucking heart attack.
ANTHONY: Yeah well I woke up to that and I woke up to hysterical crying after that in the
bathroom, for 15 minutes.
DINO: What?
ANTHONY: I woke up to that inspector calling me and I buzz in the bathroom fucking
hysterical crying. Which I noticed [Unintelligible] being her so sick bro. I see it in her face.
Looks like she aged like...
DINO and ANTHONY continue to talk about ANTHONY'S mother aging and being sick.
ANTHONY: [Unintelligible] then we made up though kicked me out of my house and
everything.
DINO: [Unintelligible] ?
ANTHONY: Yeah, she's like..
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: What she say [phonetic] ?
ANTHONY: 'Cause I borrowed six pills when it first came in. So I wasn't feeling good
so she had the... she has those things when I use to go the place you know what I mean? So I
said you know I'll get them back and then like a week later she said... 'I have enough don't worry
about it, don't go crazy for it.' So I took that as don't worry about it you don't have to get them. So
yesterday the day before yesterday she goes 'Oh I thought [phonetic] you were going to
[Unintelligible] you gonna get my things for me right? I said ' I thought you said don't worry about
it and she snapped. 'what do you mean don't worry about it you owe me six [phonetic] pounds,
what are you talking about?' Then she just didn't want to hear nothing like. She tuned into like a
fucking psycho. I'm with Paula we gotta along and your mom is downstairs. Are you there?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: Just come by later on bro.
DINO: Bye.
[End of Call]
MB:ADG
SB:JL

DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
[Cross Reference with Wire: CIII-17-2133 Call# 556]
MEDIN aka DINO TO ANTHONY
DINO: Hello.
ANTHONY: Yo, you hear me?
DINO: Yeah, what?
ANTHONY: What are you doing? You going to Brooklyn?
DINO: No.
ANTHONY: Alright, I got to take the bus to go and got my mom's sleeping pills man.
Sucks. Bro, what happened now bro, you didn't do the banister? Is it going to be ready by
Monday?
DINO: It's not going to be here by Monday.
ANTHONY: Oh bro, this is bad, did you find out what happened?
DINO: Nah.
ANTHONY: What you mean nah? Dude I have to get my mom out of here bro, she is
going to whined up fucking dying bro.
DINO: Shut up.
ANTHONY: I have to get out of here, they think it's coming Monday. So what they got to
do, call Monday?
DINO: Why you whispering for bro?
ANTHONY: Because I'm in the bathroom bro, I don't want them to hear me.
DINO: Yeah, you should just rent out her bathroom.
ANTHONY: Yeah, well, that's where I'm at most of the time. I gave her money, I had to give her
some money bro. Down to 4,000 dollars bro.
DINO: Fucking stupid bastard.
ANTHONY: Bro, what do you want me to do? I'm living on the money here. What you
want me to do. Bro, when its time to buy all this shit bro, just be ready.
DINO: Be ready for what?
ANTHONY: When it's time to buy everything?
DINO: What do you mean?
ANTHONY: Bro, what do you mean, what do you mean bro?
DINO: I don't know.
ANTHONY: Just keep putting the money aside bro. I lent you this money bro, I gave you
1,000 for yourself so...
DINO: Yo, stop fucking pressuring me.
ANTHONY: I'm not pressuring you, who's pressuring you bro? I gave you two weeks
bro, I didn't bother you at all, you didn't even come and see me or nothing bro.
DINO: I beat you.
ANTHONY: I'm saying you beat me bro.
DINO: Bro, if I beat you.
ANTHONY: [Laughs] Yeah, if I beat you down bro.
DINO: Uh-huh!
ANTHONY: And I lent your friend 200 dollars.
DINO: What?
ANTHONY: Yeah, he said, 'Please, well.... I got to get insurance.'
DINO: Are you fucking serious?
ANTHONY: Yeah bro.
DINO: What a fucking loser he is bro.
ANTHONY: Bro, you see [Unintelligible] . What he 's not good for it?
DINO: What a fucking loser.
ANTHONY: He said he didn't have no car again bro, what could I do, I have no choice neither
cause he helps me out, you know what I mean bro?
DINO: Yeah!
ANTHONY: The boilers are in at least?
DINO: Alright fuck-o, I'll talk to you later.
ANTHONY: Are they? I'm coming by when I come on the way back.
DINO: No, your not, bye.
ANTHONY: Yes, I am bye.
DINO: No, your not, bye.
ANTHONY: Yes, I am [laughs].
DINO: No your not.
ANTHONY: I'll be there at fucking 4:00.
DINO: Yeah, okay, bye.
[End of Call]
MB: PF
SB: RR

DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
MEDIN KOSIC a/k/a DINO to MIRS/1237/5875/8642
[Conversation in Albanian language in Italic]
MIRS: What's up cuz?
DINO: Yo where you at+ [Phonetic]?
MIRS: Yo, I'm on Richmond Avenue. I'm about to jump up on the expressway. Start
heading that way.
DINO: I just come out there.
MIRS: A'right then just come out.
DINO: You know what? I rather not because the car he is driving mad hot boy, my
nigga.
MIRS: Yeah but make up your mind cousin.
DINO: Yeah, but I was going, I don't want to wait in the street cuz.
MIRS: Don't want to wait in the street out there cuz. Oh, yeah, where are you,
there.
DINO: Uh-um!
MIRS: A'right. So, I'm on my way. I'm on my way now.
DINO: You gonna be like 20 minutes . You know what? I'll go by the bridge then.
MIRS: A'right. Stay by the bridge then.
DINO: A'right.
[End of Call]
SB: EJ
SB: MA
RB: GSR

Participants: DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
MEDIN KOSIC a/k/a DINO to UM5875 to JEN
[Jen answers the phone]
JEN: Hello.
DINO: Hey!
JEN: Hey! We're on our way to you. He just... somebody.. they took him down ...
on the bridge.
DINO: I might as well, get dropped off.
JEN: Uh?
DINO: I might as well, come to Staten Island.
JEN: You wanna do that?
DINO: Uh...
JEN: Let me know know so [Unintelligible] home now
DINO: A'right. yeah, I'll just come to Staten Island cause I'm not feeling waiting on
the streets all day.
JEN: I know. A'right. So, What do you want to do?
DINO: Where are you guys?
JEN: By [Unintelligible].
DINO: Tell him my friend over there, off of Hylan, he knows where.
JEN: Okay.
DINO: A'right, bye.
[End of Call]
SB: EJ
RB: MV

Participants: DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
MEDIN KOSIC a/k/a DINO to UM6760
DINO: [Aside: At the light make a left.]
UM6760: Yo.
DINO: Yo.
UM6760: Hey! What up?
DINO: Door's open?
UM6760: Oh, the upstairs door is. I don't know if downstairs is.
DINO: Well, we gonna be there in two minutes.
UM6760: All right. Let me go, do a check on it. I'll see you in a minute.
[End of Call]

DINO to GORDO
[Data on session #6679]
GORDO tells DINO that he will see him tomorrow. DINO tells GORDO that he has the money for
him and that he needs him to come do that shit. GORDO tells DINO that he doesn't need the
money that he needs the time. GORDO also says that he couldn't get everything done when he
was there and now he looking for him to finish the shit. DINO tells GORDO that he it happened
because he ran out of money. GORDO tells DINO that he got the cheapest price.

Body:
UM7150 to DINO
UM7150: Hey, what's up buddy?
DINO: What's up buddy?
UM7150: Nothing I'm here with Val... Adrian just came, so you want to come by?
DINO: Where are you?
UM7150: We at Egbert.
DINO: Yeah, till what time you staying?
UM7150: Today I don't have any plans after, so I can stay as late as you want.
DINO: A'ight yeah.

DINO: I don't know, half hour, forty minutes.
UM7150: Alright.
DINO: I gotta go home.
[Voices Overlap]
UM7150: Cause we were thinking about going to South beach.
DINO: Let me know, cause I just have to stop home and get dressed.
UM7150: Alright, we'll wait for you here and then if anything we go down there together.
DINO: Alright bye.
UM7150: Alright bye.
[End Of Call]

Body:
UM2597 (Dad) to DINO
[Conversation in Albanian in Italic]
DINO: Hello!
UM2597: Hey, Where are you?
DINO: Why? What's the matter?
UM2597: Nothing, nothing. When you called, I... I ... listen, I didn't want to go [Unintelligible]
[mumbling]
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: That's alright.
[Voices Overlap]
UM2597: I left early before two o'clock and dropped the clothes to be washed.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: That's okay, don't worry. It's alright.
[Voices Overlap]
UM2597: No, no, just want to tell you. Linda called me and asked, ' Dad where are you?'
And I said, ' I am going to get the clothes.' ' Okay' , she said, ' I am coming and lets go
out somewhere in New Jersey and [unintelligible]. ' Then she said, ' [Unintelligible]. I had no
idea that we were going out. '
DINO: Alright.
UM2597: Are you coming tomorrow at ...
DINO: No
UM2597: No, alright, bye.
[End Of Call]

DINO: So fucking ridiculous, bro!

MIRS: Southern Bank Hills [Phonetic]
DINO: Do I know anybody that knows her?
MIRS: I don't know, cuz. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know, cuz. I don't
know. I don't know, cuz. I have no plan. I don't know, cuz. I'm lost, cuz. I'm lost, cuz.

MIRS: I'm waiting, cuz. I'm just waiting to see when it [Pause] if it pops up. I gave them, I

[Voices Overlap]

took them. She counted wrong. The days were mixed up and she snapped out. 'I want to die.'
Screaming, fucking yelling at me. Fucking... forget it, bro. Just get me out of here, bro. Get my

don't you come here for? You don't come here no more, at all.

[Voices Overlap]

[Voices Overlap]

DINO: No, that's not what I plan on doing. But if he gives you a 1,000 dollars dude,
that's 1,000 dollars off my bill.
ANTHONY: What do you mean 1,000 dollars off your bill?
DINO: He's gotta give me a Section 8 check for this month.
ANTHONY: Oh, he's giving you that for this month? He said that?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: Oh, so get it from him bro. What the fuck man?
DINO: No, I told him to give it to you.
ANTHONY: Give it to me?
DINO: Yeah. What's the difference?
ANTHONY: Because he ain't gonna fucking come here, bro. He's supposed to come
here today. Where is he? He said he was supposed to pick me up and we are gonna come over
to see you, he said. I called him up. He said he'll call you right back and he never called back
and he told me the fucking U-haul truck was 600 dollars.
DINO: No, he told me 4.
ANTHONY: He told me 600.
DINO: No, he told me 4.
ANTHONY: He told me 6 then I go, 'Joe, you know that money, man? I would never lie
to you bro. That I miscounted.' I said, 'There was 500 missing, bro. We were going to do
something about that, right?' He goes, 'Yeah, I'll pick you up.' When did he call me? Uh,
Saturday he called me. Oh you he called you up. Right after he called you and called me up. He
said, 'I just spoke to Dino, 'Blah, blah, blah, blah.' He said, 'The U-haul bill was 600.' I said,
'600?'
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: He told me 4.
ANTHONY: Yeah, I know. He just lied. That right there, he's a liar.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: 600 for what?
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: That's what I said. I said, 'For what?' I said, 'The truck was only 3 days
late.' He goes, 'No, the mileage on it.' I said, 'The mileage? What we really did, drive from
Brooklyn to his house, and then I drove it to my Aunt's.'
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: And I told him it was going to be like 50 miles. That's not 50 miles.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Yeah, so 50 miles is only 200 dollars, bro. So say, 200 and 200... it should
be 400, like you said. 400. It should be around that.
DINO: That's what he said.
ANTHONY: He told me 6. So, I don't know. That means he's a liar. If he did that, if you
told you 4 and told me 6. Maybe he was just getting riled up to fucking, to get you fucking... what
you call? To make you look stupid. He's like, 'Oh, Dino, I don't know what he did with the truck. '
I got the bill. I got the what you call you call it? The notification. I'm like what the hell is this? He
actually paid it fucking like Friday or something. He waited that long, if anything maybe he got
late charges for not paying it. How the hell did get his card anyway? [Pause] You there?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: Yeah, [Stammers] how did they put it? The only way we were all able to get
the truck, right?
DINO: Yep.
ANTHONY: Cause he put it on his card?
DINO: I guess so.
ANTHONY: I don't know. I thought we were going to get away with it. Alright, so what
he's doing? Putting up the thing tomorrow?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: [Stammers] I gotta ask the inspector, is there electricity in the house right
now?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: Because the other guy, when I talked to him Friday... He said, one of the
reasons why it could be... because he didn't know what was going on. He said the electricity has
to be turned on. You know what I mean? Leave it on until I get there and then we'll switch it over.
That's one of the thing, electricity and gas has to be working or else they'll fail it. The stove works
too?
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: So that's all that has to be done right now, it's the stair case? It's the dent?
The Bannister?
DINO: Yeah, and the water heater.
ANTHONY: So, they said they did the water heater all this time.
DINO: Alright, don't worry about it. Bye.
ANTHONY: I'm not worried about it. Just fucking do everything for my mom, Dino.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: I am. It's [Unintelligible] , bro.
ANTHONY: Yeah. [Chuckles]
[End of Call]

Body:
ANTHONY (Using DOLORES's phone) to DINO
ANTHONY tells DINO that when he turned the light off on the microwave, by accident he hit the
wrong button and he woke her (Probably his mother) up, and she snapped. ANTHONY reminds
DINO that they (Him, his mother and aunt) have to get out, because they've been there a month
already. ANTHONY tells DINO that he told him that in two days and wants to know what
happened. DINO tells ANTHONY that the appointment for the boiler is tomorrow. ANTHONY
asks when is the Inspector going. DINO tells ANTHONY not to worry about it. ANTHONY tells
DINO that they're getting kicked out and then they'll be going to DINO's house by the end of the
week. DINO tells ANTHONY that there's no room at his place. ANTHONY repeats that his
mother's 85 years old and this situation is killing her. DINO tells ANTHONY that he's going as
fast as he can. ANTHONY asks then why isn't it ready. DINO tells ANTHONY that they have to put
in the boilers and tie them in and that's it.
ANTHONY asks DINO again when is the Inspection, and what is he going to tell them (Probably
his mother and aunt). ANTHONY tells DINO that he [D] has to go over to him [A] and talk to her
(His mother) because he's not talking anymore. DINO tells ANTHONY that he doesn't have to go
there to talk to anyone.
DINO hangs up the phone.
[End of Call]

Body:
MEDIN a/k/a DINO to UM2597 [Dino' father]
[Conversation in Albanian in Italic]
UM2597: Hello.
DINO: Did they come to work today? What?
UM2597: Hello,
DINO: It is Din, Did they come to work today?
UM2597: Yes, they are downstairs.
DINO: Okay. You called me before?
UM2597: Yes I did. I called you to take me to therapy. but you didn't answer. I called two three
times.
DINO: Okay. All right.
UM2597: All right. Okay. Bye.
[End of call]
SB: CR

Participants: DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
MEDIN KOSIC a/k/a DINO to UF0606 (maternal Aunt)
[Conversation in Albanian in Italic]
UF0606: Hello.
DINO: Hello.
UF0606: Hey dear what are you doing?
DINO: What're you doing?
UF0606: Nothing, how are you , are you well?
DINO: Well, thanks God and you?
UF0606: Well, thanks God, what're you doing?
DINO: Oh, nothing, home.
UF0606: Yeah?
DINO: Yeah.
UF0606: That's good then. That's good.
DINO: How's everybody?
UF0606: Good, good, thanks God.
DINO: All right. The kids, good?
UF0606: Everybody good. Thank God. Everybody. I called to see how you doing.
DINO: I'm good. I'm good.
UF0606: That's good. That's good.
DINO: Yes. Yeah. Anyway. What else can I do? Just...
UF0606: What have done?
DINO: Quite well.
UF0606: How's your father?
DINO: He's good, he's good.
UF0606: That's good.
DINO: He's downstairs.
UF0606: That's good. What are you doing, tired?
DINO: Yeah, well, a little bit. Yeah.
UF0606: Yeah.
DINO: Stressing out. That's it.
UF0606: What?
DINO: Just stressed.
UF0606: Why, my dear? What is it?
DINO: Nah, just, you know, got a lot done fast, you know.
UF0606: Huh?
DINO: I did a lot of work here really fast, so.
UF0606: Do it step by step.
DINO: Yeah.
UF0606: Did you give that other side?
DINO: Huh?
UF0606: You gave that side.
DINO: I didn't start. I didn't start it yet. I just finished putting the boilers for this side.
UF0606: Oh. Work slowly son.
DINO: Yeah. Oh, Auntie what slowly, we are living here for 30 years now, it doesn't make any
sense any more step by step. I am angry...
[Voice overlapping]
UF0606: Auntie, you have to finish it!
DINO: You know, I just want it to finish and get it over with.
UF0606: We have to work all our life as long as we live.
DINO: Huh?
UF0606: We have to work all our life.
DINO: I know, I know.
UF0606: One way or the other, we have to work.
DINO: What are you gonna do?
UF0606: Nothing, what to do.
DINO: Where are you, home?
UF0606: I am out to buy some stuff. We go to farm to get some stuff.
DINO: Oh, okay.
UF0606: We are picking ourselves.
DINO: What, like apples and orange? Like apples and stuff, right?
UF0606: No, everything there, everything.
DINO: Oh, really?
UF0606: You have vegetables there, eggplants, peppers, tomatoes, potatoes, everything.
DINO: Nice!
UF0606: Everything.
DINO: Jersey's nice.
UF0606: Huh?
DINO: Jersey is nice. I said Jersey is nice.
UF0606: Yeah, it is not far from us, I better go there and pick them fresh myself.
DINO: Yeah, clean there, life is cleaner over there
UF0606: I know.
DINO: I think so. Over here, you know, you know I am fed up
UF0606: Eh, I know
DINO: I am fed up There's no privacy. Everyone is so close to each other.
UF0606: I know.
DINO: Yeah.
UF0606: What can you do? I know.
DINO: All right.
UF0606: I called to see how you are doing?
DINO: Yeah, thank you, thank you.
UF0606: Eh what else
DINO: Oh, man. I was gonna come that day and nobody told me.
UF0606: Yeah?
DINO: If I was told I should have come, but no one told me anything,?
UF0606: I don't know.
DINO: Oh, well. Yeah.
UF0606: Yeah next time.
DINO: Yeah, I promise I will.
UF0606: Yeah. I hope.
DINO: Yeah.
UF0606: Yeah my dear
DINO: All right.
UF0606: Thank you and say hello to father and hope to meet soon.
DINO: Okay. Hey, I wanted to tell you something.
UF0606: Huh?
DINO: Mir...Mirsad, he got....he went to jail again.
UF0606: Mirsad went to jail again?
DINO: Mmm-hmm. It was on the computer.
UF0606: He deserves that, let him stay there for a long time.
DINO: Yeah.
UF0606: Good enough, good enough, Nice thing.
DINO: Yeah, I don't know, he was caught with everything
UF0606: I tried to call but nobody answered. I talked to Betty [Phonetic] too today and she
doesn't know and she was worried about him but he is back in the hole.
DINO: Yeah, it's bad this time.
UF0606: Ah. You know...
DINO: It's bad.
UF0606: He's never gonna learn.
DINO: Nope.
UF0606: With those things, you cannot get away.
DINO: Nope.
UF0606: No, no. Eh he...He's better off there.
DINO: Yeah.
UF0606: He's better off. He's better off. I swear to god, because I don't know what to say no
more. I don't know
DINO: What can you say? At the end of the day, you have to watch yourself.
UF0606: That's it. That's it.
DINO: You know, listen, if you don't watch yourself no one can protect you.
[Voices overlapping] [Noises on the background]
UF0606: That's right, that's right. I hope he has a good life? Don't know what else I can tell?
DINO: What good life inside?
UF0606: Better inside that being killed by someone outside.
DINO: Yeah, you know
UF0606: For him, it is better off there.
DINO: You know.
UF0606: For him he is better off there.
DINO: Yeah, you're right with that.
UF0606: For him.
DINO: Yes.
UF0606: 'Cause anyway, any day you waiting for some bad news from him.
DINO: Always.
UF0606: Yeah, so he's better off there.
DINO: Always.
UF0606: [Unintelligible] What are you gonna do? That's life.
DINO: When you don't care for yourself.

Body:
JOE to MEDIN a/k/a DINO
Voicemail Reached Message Left
JOE: Dino. I called you yesterday a few times. I left you a message. I been in your driveway
since 10:45. It's 11:30 now. Anthony's been knocking on the door. I been knocking on your
window. Uh, give me a call back. We got a problem here. Nothing is done. Nothing is
connected. The boilers aren't connected. Railing's not up yet. Uh... we had an arrangement.
We had a deal. I made Anthony a promise. And his mother. You know? And you made a
promise. Uh... also, he gave you the money. A'ight. Give me a call please. Thank you.
[End of Message ]
SB:GMS
RB: PF

Body:
RACHEL TO MEDIN aka DINO
RACHEL: What do you want? What's up?
DINO: What do you want?
RACHEL: You are calling in, and she said, 'You calling?' I said, 'I'll call you back when I can.'
What's up?
DINO: I don't know. She said you wanted to go over there to pick up his clothes.
[Voices Overlap]
RACHEL: I don't want to go nothing. You're fucking cousin made me go out of my way to fuckin
go to that hotel and leave work, and then have everything done. Now I gotta run around and pick
up everybody and drop off over there. [Stutters] What the fuck is the problem?
DINO: Nothing.
RACHEL: I can do it on my own and I'll bring it to you. How about that? Huh?
DINO: Uh...
[Voices Overlap]
RACHEL: Otherwise, when he calls me back, I'll tell him that you and princess Jen can go.
DINO: What is your problem dude?
RACHEL: [Chuckles]
DINO: I didn't want you do nothing. Did I make you take off and go out of your way
to go get somebody's shit?
[Voices Overlap]
RACHEL: I don't like be talking to, I don't like being talked to like I'm customer and I don't like to
be asked to do something because it's so desperate that his fucking wife won't answer the
phone and he needs somebody to help him do it and I gotta want to do it like it's important and
all of a sudden... all of a sudden she was going to go and yous gotta go because I'm not feeling
it. It's better if yous do it. Fuck it.
DINO: Where are you?

DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
MEDIN a/k/a DINO to UM2410
[ Conversation in Albanian in Italic]
UM: Hello?
DINO: What's up, uncle [ maternal]
UM: Hey. What's doing, man?
DINO: What're u doing?
UM: Well and you, what have u done?
DINO: A'right. Are you well?
UM: Not bad, son. And you?
DINO: A'right.
UM: What're u doing?
DINO: Nothing actually. About to go pick up some stuff from Home Depot.
[Voices Overlap]
UM: Oh okay.
DINO: Yeah. Uh...I'm just the messenger here. Uhm... Mirsad's wife called me. And she told
me to tell you that he went to court today. And they told him fourteen years to life.
UM: A'ight
DINO: I don't know why she told me to tell you. But, that's what it is. So, I don't know if she's
expecting help from anybody I can't help nobody. I can't help myself. So...
UM: [Stutters] I cannot help my fucking self no more. Just help himself.
DINO: I hear you. That's what she told me they offered him. Fourteen years to life. The
lawyers... He owes a lawyer like thirty five thousand dollars. Plus the fees just to get him out is
like twenty five thousand dollars. It's like sixty, seventy thousand dollars, dude. [Pause] [Sighs] I
don't know. He wants to cry about it now.
UM: A'ight, man.
DINO: I'm sorry to bother you, man.
UM: When he had the court?
DINO: Yesterday.
UM: Where did they take him ?
DINO: Riker's Island.
UM: Yeah?
DINO: Yeah. [Pause] Fuck! He should have thought about that. I don't know. I don't know.
He thinks that people... everybody's gonna get up and help him. He burnt everybody. So, I don't
know if you wanna talk to your brother. I don't know, dude. I don't wanna be in the middle of this.
I'm just telling you 'cause that's some serious shit.
UM: No help from my side. I did enough in my life for him. So... I mean, wish I
can help him. But, at the end of the day, I cannot help myself.
DINO: I don't know.
UM: That's what he wanna do. That's what he does. You know. He wanna
play. That's what he gets.
DINO: He's running around fucking smoking drugs all day in a car, man.
UM: Mmm. [Unintelligible] I don't know what to tell you.
DINO: No. No. No. You don't have to tell me anything, dude. I'm not calling you. I'm not
asking you for anything. I'm just telling you just so you know. 'Cause honestly I don't wanna be
the one to call uncle Ram [Phonetic] I'm not... Yeah... I'm definitely not calling him and telling him
anything. So, I'm sorry. I'm gonna leave that to you.
UM: [Sighs] A'ight, man
DINO: A'ight? I'm sorry.
UM: A'ight. See you.
DINO: Okay. Bye.
[End of Call]

DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] DOLORES and ANTHONY KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
ANTHONY to MEDIN a/k/a DINO
DINO: [Aside: Jesus Christ!]
ANTHONY: Yo!
DINO: Yo.
ANTHONY: Yeah. You gotta come here, bro. You gotta come pick me up. They kicked
us out.
DINO: What do you mean I gotta come? And put you where?
ANTHONY: I'm gonna stay with you. I was talking to my mom to go stay with Ella. They
kicked us out. Told you, bro. Did he put the banister up?
DINO: He's doing everything this weekend.
ANTHONY: Well, they want us out.
DINO: I haven't even been home in like five or six days.
ANTHONY: Why? So, why don't you let me and my mom stay there then? In your
house.
DINO: Yeah. Let you and your mom stay there.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: It's a mess. Right? Yeah. Why not? Why not? At least she'll clean the
house and everything. Clean up.
DINO: I don't understand how mother just got kicked out.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: Yeah. I know. I know. Whatever.
DINO: What the fuck could you guys possibly be doing now?
ANTHONY: Nothing at all. It's just they're crazy. They kicked Ella out, remember? The
same thing. I don't wanna stay with Ella. Ella's a little bit.... Right? And I'll stay at your house.
And then if my mom could stay with Ella. 'Cause they don't want her there long either. And then
she'll come with me. They should be done Mon...by the weekend and we'll call Monday.
Tomorrow you could call and set it up for Monday. You know?
DOLORES: [Background: Who you talking to?]
ANTHONY: [Aside: To Dino.]
DOLORES: [Background: Tell Dino [Unintelligible] ]
ANTHONY: See? She's crying! See Dino? [Aside: You're not going in the street,
Ma. Stop crying. Wow! Wow! ]
DOLORES: [Background: [Crying] [Unintelligible] ]
ANTHONY: [Aside: You are not going to the street, ma. ]
DINO: Going in the street for what?
ANTHONY: [Aside: Ma! Where you going? Stop. Go Relax. Go fucking relax.]
DOLORES: [Background: [Crying] [Screamns] Leave me alone. [Unintelligible]. ]
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: [Aside: I'm not doing this. You're gonna have a fucking heart attack.
A'right, Ma. Stop. Oh God.]
DOLORES: [Background: [Crying] [Unintelligible] ]
ANTHONY: Hello? [Aside: Relax, Ma! Stop. We have a place to go. Threre's
nowhere for you to go. Stop! Stop! Relax! Relax!]
DOLORES: [Background Dolores: Oh God! Help me!]
ANTHONY: [Aside: Relax! Relax! Relax! Relax! Ma. You're not going in the street. ]
[Call disconnects]
[End of Call]

Body:
ANTHONY to MEDIN a/k/a DINO
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: Yeah, tell mom we got to come over there.
DINO: Come over where?
ANTHONY: To your house, I got nowhere to go.
DINO: Alright.
ANTHONY: And mom is going to go to Ella's. You hear her crying, they kicked us out bro, we
got until tomorrow. [PAUSE] Dino.
DINO: I don't know dude, I haven't been home in 4-5 days.
ANTHONY: Alright, so. Bro, this is bad Dino, my mother is 85, she is just going to be
just wandering around, place to place. Its not good man.
DINO: Yeah, wandering around.
ANTHONY: Yeah, Dino what are you talking about? She has nowhere to live bro.
DINO: Okay.
ANTHONY: So what's up? Why can't it be done tomorrow?
DINO: Why can't what be done tomorrow?
ANTHONY: Finish the banister.
DINO: He's going to come when he's going to come, that's it, that's what he told me. This
weekend.
ANTHONY: Bro, listen to me Dino.
DINO: So he's finishing up with them now, he's doing when the fuck he can do it dude.
ANTHONY: Dino, why are you talking to me like that?
DINO: Because don't give me more fucking stress dude.
ANTHONY: What?
DINO: Don't get me stressed out.
ANTHONY: Don't get you stressed? Are you kidding me, mother is fucking having a heart...
DINO: What do you want me to do? I got to worry about my heart dude.
ANTHONY: You got to worry about yours? Yeah, remember this apartment should have been
done already, are you kidding me right now?
DINO: Yeah, 'Oh, this apartment should have been done already, right, right, right? Yeah,
yeah, yeah.' Yeah, I know dude.
ANTHONY: Bro, are you fucking... are you serious right now.
DINO: Yeah, I am fucking serious dude.
ANTHONY: Are you serious?
DINO: You got some fucking balls to get up and tell me how it should have been done
already, yeah, I know.
ANTHONY: Are you shitting me? What are you talking about? What are you kidding
me?
No response
[End of Call]

MIRS (NYC DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS) to DINO
[Conversation in Albanian in italic]
A/R: This is a free call from... an inmate at New York City Department of Correction. This
call is subject to recording and monitoring.
MIRS: Hello.
DINO: Hey!
MIRS: What's up, cuz?
DINO: What's up?
MIRS: Nothing. What are you doing?
DINO: Nothing. I'm in Brooklyn.
MIRS: No doubt.
DINO: What's going on?
MIRS: Nothing, just called.
DINO: Yeah.
MIRS: Just called.
DINO: Alright. What's up?
MIRS: Nothing, nothing.
DINO: [Sighs] [Audio Glitch] Unbelievable [Pause] Have they told you anything or?
MIRS: I don't know, cuz. What to tell, cuz.
DINO: I don't know.
MIRS: What to tell? Cuz. I don't know what to say anymore, cuz. [Pause] They
would like you to talk to who I said to talk to.
DINO: Yes. Like I said, as soon as I get a chance. I know where his house is. Should I go
knock on his door? Or I have his number, no?
MIRS: Yeah. My wife has his number. But I don't know, my wife... who she is
anymore, cuz. I don't know who that girl is anymore. [Background: Noise/voices] [Pause] I think I
lost somebody that, I think I pushed somebody, I don't know, man. I think I did that to myself, cuz. I
got rid of somebody very good in my life. [Pause] I don't know. I don't know, cuz. I'm all fucked up
right now, cuz. I don't know what to think anymore.
DINO: She is there ...
[Voices overlap]
MIRS: I don't know what she thinks... What she's thinking. What she's doing or...
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: She is home , cuz. She's not going anywhere. You know what I mean? She is home.
MIRS: I know, cuz. I need my wife, I need my wife to be back to who she is, cuz.
[Pause] I turned my wife into an animal, cuz. I made my wife , I forced my wife to use drugs, cuz.
DINO: Crazy, cuz.
MIRS: That hurts, cuz. I did that to her, cuz.
[Audio Glitch]
DINO: [Pause] [Sighs] It's bad, cuz.
MIRS: What?
DINO: It's bad, cuz. Thank God, at least she's not dead.
[Voices overlap]
MIRS: What?
[Voices overlap]
DINO: At least she's not doing the other thing.
MIRS: I know, cuz. But that's bad, cuz. What I [Audio breaks] my wife does.
[Voices overlap]
DINO: I know, cuz. I'm trying, cuz. I'm trying, cuz. But I can't control her. What do you want me
to beat her?
[Voices overlap]
MIRS: No cuz, keep her under control cuz. Tell her yo.
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Beat her, cuz?
MIRS: No, cuz. Control that, cuz please.
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Eh , cuz? That's [Stutters] the only thing.
[Voices overlap]
MIRS: Tell her, 'You don't know what you're doing to husband.' Yo, you don't know
what's she's doing to me, cuz. You don't know, you don't if I mess with someone here inside,
cuz. And I could never come out. [Pause] Alright, cuz? You know what it means to break the
phone here right?
DINO: Huh?
MIRS: You know what it is to break a phone in here, right?
DINO: Yeah.
MIRS: Alright. I broke two of them already.
DINO: Oh Gosh.
MIRS: I got into... maybe. I'm about to go in my fourth fight already, cuz. [Pause] I'm
on my third ticket already.
DINO: [Sighs]
MIRS: [Pause] I'm loosing it, cuz. I'm bugging out, cuz. I'm [Stutters] becoming
[Stutters] Devil, cuz. I am becoming bad, very bad, cuz. I don't know who I am anymore.
DINO: I don't know. [Stutters] I...
[Voices overlap]
MIRS: I'm like a lion in a, I'm like a lion in cage, right now cuz. I'm bugging out, cuz.
[Pause] I'm scared of myself right now, cuz.
DINO: [Sighs] Don't think like that, cuz. 'Cause you know [Stutters] she's you know. She's
looking to fucking sit there and making sure that you feel like fucking dick.
MIRS: Uh?
DINO: She's looking to make you feel like a fucking dick. You know she's fucking pissed too.
MIRS: I know but, it won't bite.
[Voices overlap]
DINO: It's just a bad situation, dude. Bad situation. Terrible situation. But my heart...
[Voices overlap]
A/R: You have one minute left.
DINO: My heart drops, cuz.
[Voices overlap]
MIRS: Alright, cuz. I gotta call you back. I gotta call you back. But uh...
[Voices overlap]
DINO: You know that woman, Rachel, she had the money, I told her to send the money.
MIRS: Alright. But my clothes and my sneakers, and everything. She's dubbing
[Phonetic] my phone calls. Nobody's answering my phone calls. I'll call later, cuz. When my time
comes back.
DINO: [Sighs] Alright.
MIRS: Alright?
DINO: But we got...
[Voices Overlap]
MIRS: I got last... I got last slot, so... 15 minutes to 9:00 is my last phone call
though on the whole island so.
DINO: Where are you? What uh, building?
MIRS: I'm in C-95 Projects, cuz. 'High Classification'.
DINO: Okay. Have you seen anyone there?
MIRS: Nicky, I saw Nicky. Chris, or whatever the fuck his name is.
DINO: Really you saw him?
MIRS: Yeah, I seen him. He's upstairs from me.
DINO: Did you talk to him?
MIRS: Yeah, yeah. I was on a bus with him and everything. I stood with him all day
in the bullpen.
DINO: Is he alright?
MIRS: Yeah, he's alright. He's alright [Chuckles]. He got a full flat. He's good. He's
good. Looks better [Audio breaks] [Unintelligible] ...
[Voices overlap]
A/R: Thank you for using Securess. Good-bye.
[End of Call]

ANTHONY (IDed in Session ) [FORMERLY UM5250] DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
DOLORES [Using Anthony's phone] to MEDIN a/k/a DINO
[Cross Reference with Wire: CIII-17-2133 Call# 1412]
DINO: Hello? Hello?
DOLORES: Hi, Dino.
DINO: Hi Ma.
DOLORES: What are you doing?
DINO: Nah. I'm working.
DOLORES: Working?
DINO: Yeah.
DOLORES: Awww. You take time off to eat?
DINO No. Who got time for that, ma?
DOLORES: You haven't got time?!
DINO: Nah.
DOLORES: Well... you eat beef frankfurters?
DINO: [Chuckles] Yeah.
DOLORES: I got beef frankfurters.
DINO: That's a'right, ma. You don't worry about nothing.
DOLORES: Ahhh. I got them. I got food here I'm taking.
DINO: I'm okay.
DOLORES: A'right. Listen.
DINO: Hah?
[Voices Overlap]
DOLORES: They want me out of here at 6:00. So, I gotta come there at 6:00. Okay?
You could work. You know? You could work. I'm not gonna stop you.
DINO: Uh... Uh... Ask them if they could give you 'til like 7:00 or 8:00.
DOLORES: They won't give me it. They told me 6:00.
DINO: A'ight. A'ight. No problem.
DOLORES: I just don't wanna curse on the phone.
DINO: That's okay.
DOLORES: I'm gonna get there in a car service. Okay?
DINO: Okay Where's Anthony?
DOLORES: He's putting the stuff in... my food in the bag.
DINO: A'ight. You got it.
[Voices Overlap]
DOLORES: Okay. I'll see you later, babe.
DINO: A'right.
DOLORES: Bye
DINO: Bye
[End of Call]

DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] DOLORES and ANTHONY KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
MEDIN a/k/a DINO to ANTHONY
ANTHONY: Hello? Yo!
DINO: What's up, bro?
ANTHONY: Nothing. I'm worried, man. Ridiculous. I hate my life right now, man. The
guy came?
DINO Yeah.
ANTHONY: A'ight. Did he put the wood on the plywood up?
DINO: No.
ANTHONY: I could do that, bro. We could do that. You got a fucking skill-saw. Right?
[Voices Overlap] .
DINO: Nah. Alll.... Nah. All he did... he got up.. he drilled the holes for the vents. And he
drilled the holes for the banister. He promised me for Monday.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: A'ight. So, that's just....
DINO: He promised me Monday morning it's all gonna be in. So... and then Tuesday the
electrician is coming to wire up the boilers and shit.
ANTHONY: A'ight. I gotta fucking.... I'll put this stuff in the... in the new house. In the new
apartment. The bags we got. You know. Clothes. All my mom's clothes and shit. My ... I only
got one. The bag of dirty clothes. A big, big bag I have to wash.
DINO: A'ight. Fucking my cleaning lady just came back from fucking... from Albania just
now. Today. [Unintelligible]
ANTHONY: My mother will just straighten up. Don't worry about it.
DINO: Yeah. Well, a lot of straightening up.
ANTHONY: Just don't leave like... Just do a little thing. Like if there's food there. Just
put that away.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Little thing what? I'm out. Ready to go, dude. That's why I didn't wanna go there.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: A'ight. A'ight. So, I'll leave...
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: So, don't fucking bitch and complain then. I don't wanna hear nothing.
ANTHONY: A'ight. So, liste. Uh... do you wanna leave the key in the boiler room?
DINO: I did leave it there. I did leave it there.
ANTHONY: Where?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: I left it in the mailbox.
ANTHONY: In the mailbox?
DINO: But, the only thing is I don't have a door handle on my door.
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: I know that.
DINO: The thing broke. I gotta put in a new one.
ANTHONY: I know
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: A'ight. So, I'll give you the combination. The number.
ANTHONY: Oh. You wanna text it?
DINO: Yeah. That's a'ight. I'll tell you when you get there.
ANTHONY: A'ight. So, what is uh.... You're not gonna be there then? [Pause] Hello?
[Pause] Hello? [Pause] Yo!
DINO: Yeah?
ANTHONY: You're not gonna be there?
DINO: No. Figure it out, cuz.
ANTHONY: No. I know that. But, I'm saying. You're not gonna be there?
DINO: No.
ANTHONY: And when you coming back? Tomorrow?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: I don't know. I don't know. Probably, yeah. Tomorrow.
ANTHONY: I heard what happened.
DINO: Mikey?
ANTHONY: Yeah.
DINO: Oh my God!
ANTHONY: That's crazy!
DINO: Yup. Well, anyways... I'm driving.
ANTHONY: He thinks he's a Gotti. He thought. [Phonetic]
DINO: Well, I'll talk to you when I see you.
ANTHONY: A'ight
[End of Call]
SB:GMS

Body:
MEDIN a/k/a DINO to KATHY
KATHY: Hello?
DINO: Yeah?
KATHY: What?
DINO: You called me twice.
KATHY: Who's this? [Pause] It's the phone! It's the phone! I didn't mean to call you.
Someone was trying to hack into my.....
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Who's you?
KATHY: Huh?
DINO: Who's you?
KATHY: It's me! Kathy! Who's this?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Okay. And who am I?
KATHY: Who are you?
DINO: I don't know
KATHY: Is it.... Does your name begin with a 'D'?
DINO: Yeah. Dickhead. [Laughs]
KATHY: A'right. Dino. No. Listen to what happened. .Someone was trying to hack into my
Facebook.
DINO: Oh God.
KATHY: So I had Verizon on the phone with me all day. I would say I wasted two freaking hours
of my day. Because someone was trying to get in Facebook and it even said it. From uh,
Jersey that someone was trying to hack into... And I called Verizon. Verizon says to me, 'Is
there anyone that don't like you that knows your phone number?' I says 'Of course. Doesn't
everyone have that?' And she says, 'No.' So, in any case. Uhm... they're still working on it.
Not the phone part. There's nothing on my phone. They went through my phone. They said but
someone was trying to get into the Facebook. So, that's that.
DINO: Wow!
KATHY: What?
DINO: A'ight. Let me go. 'Cause I'm driving.
KATHY: It's probably him up the street. His kids. They got nothing to do in their life. They don't
have no friends. No girlfriends. No nothing.
[End of Call]

Body:
UM8071 [to MEDIN a/k/a DINO
(Conversation in Albanian Language in italic)
DINO: Hello
UM8071: Yo!
DINO: What's up, cuz?
UM8071: What's up, bro? Where you been?
DINO: What u doing?
UM8071: I been trying to call you for two days, bro.
DINO: I know, cuz. I been so busy. I been so stressed out. Fuck it
[Voices Overlap]
UM8071: What's going on?
DINO: Fuck it
UM8071: Why u stressed out, what's going on bro?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Everything
UM8071: Come. Come by my house and relieve some stress.
DINO: Are u Okay?
UM8071: Yeah. Yeah. What're u doing? Where are u?
DINO: Nothing, bro. I'm working right now. But, I'm trying to go home right now to go get
dressed. Take a shower and head out.
UM8071: Uh, head out. Where you headed out to? You're coming here. Right?
DINO: Yeah. Yeah.
UM8071: A'ight. I'll see you by the house.
DINO: Oh. Okay. You will be there 'till when
UM8071: Uh.. 10:30.. 11:00. I'm not trying to make it too late.
DINO: Oh you getting old man
UM8071: Old, Well, you know. [Chuckles]
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Wake u early in the morning?
UM8071: Yeah. No. I'm good. Wake these guys in the morning not me. A'ight?
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: Okay. Okay. You got it, cuz. A'ight.
UM8071: A'ight, Dino. I'll see you by the house. Bye.
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: A'ight. Bye.
[End of Call]

Body:
DINO to FATJON KALLUGIERI
[Conversation in Albanian Language in italic]
FATJON: Hey.
DINO: Hey dick.
FATJON: Hey dick, what u doing?
DINO: Where are u?
FATJON: Here to get the bride, where are u?
DINO: Oh, man.
FATJON: Hey dick, get up. Enough sleeping.
DINO: All right.
FATJON: What are those video you dick ?
DINO: Yo, what was I gonna say? Uh... the wedding is in Jersey, right?
FATJON: Yeah.
DINO: Oh, shit. All right. [Pause] Fuck.
FATJON: Why?
DINO: I'm heading out now, man.
FATJON: Heading where? But we gonna stay home, get dressed, get ready for the wedding.
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Nah, whatever. How did everything go, good? Right.
FATJON: Huh?
DINO: How did everything go good, good?
FATJON: Yeah.
DINO: Alright.
FATJON: Alright, bro.
DINO: Uh, where's Elvis? He went over there?
FATJON: Elvis's home. Elvin might come with me. [Pause] [Clears his throat] So, [Stutters] I
think he's going with Val.
DINO: Okay, bye.
FATJON: Alright, peace.
[End of Call]

ready for a wedding today.

night.

UM0214: Yeah, fuck it , fuck it.
[Dino laughs]

UM0214: Right now we're going back to Afrim [PH] to bring bride home, have a shower and g

DINO and UM say that they will see each other at the wedding and the wedding is taking place

DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
[Digits Appear on Session # 10645]
Outgoing: 646-966-9314
DINO to ANTHONY
ANTHONY: Mikey.
DINO: What's up?
ANTHONY: What's wrong, Mike? You fucked up, bro.
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Why you calling me Mikey for? My cleaning lady hasn't been around in two months,
dude.
[Voices overlap]
ANTHONY: Yeah, no that's [Stutters] well... bro. [Stutters] I did the bathroom, right?
Three hours, bro. I cleaned the bathroom sparkling, bro.
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Yeah, alright. Good for you. Well, you don't wanna, you don't wanna go...
[Voices overlap]
ANTHONY: Now listen...
[Voices overlap]
DINO: You wanna go somewhere else?
[Voices overlap]
ANTHONY: Now listen, bro, listen. Uh, you have allergies? Your father snapped. 'Cause
[Stutters] there's no cold water in the shower. So [Stutters] I knocked on the tenants door.
DINO: Yeah.
ANTHONY: No one answered upstairs. Banging, nothing, you know, 'Whoa, whoa,
whoa', no one answered. So I shut the water-main off. And I guess they called you fa, you know,
your father came over. So then I told him. He said, 'Oh, why did you do that, why?' I said,
'Because there's no hot, you know, only cold water. I can't really clean the shower good.'
[Voices overlap]
DINO: Yeah. The fucking... the whatyoumaycallit. The fucking uh...
[Voices overlap]
ANTHONY: I have to adjust it. But I need 'Alekies' [Phonetic]. You have any?
DINO: I don't know.
ANTHONY: Alright, anyway. Tell your father that I'm gonna fix it later, then. 'Cause he
wants, he wants to hear it from you. He says, 'Oh, you gotta tell Dino first.' He got mad. [Stutters]
He's just a cranky old man.
DINO: Yeah. Alright, du...
[Voices overlap]
ANTHONY: So tell your dad, alright? Call him and tell him. I'll walk to that store later. I'll
go get 'Alekies' [Phonetic] at that uh, at that thrift store over there.
DINO: You guys doing alright?
ANTHONY: Yeah, bro. We're cleaning stuff.
DINO: Oh wow. And you know what's crazy? That fucking lady went to Albania for two
months. She calls me yesterday, 'I'm back'.
ANTHONY: Bro, your clothes... is a pile up to three feet high. And I put it all in one pile.
DINO: Yeah, I know. Are you comfortable?
[Voices overlap]
ANTHONY: Yeah, now we are.
DINO: Alright, well what the fuck?
[Voices Overlap]
ANTHONY: I cleaned until 5:00. My mother went to sleep at 3:00. I cleaned 'til 5:00.
DINO: Alright. Alright, you got it.
[Voices overlap]
ANTHONY: Just tell your dad, alright?
DINO: Alright, bye.
ANTHONY: Bye.
[End of Call]
SB: TP
RB: PF

Participants: DINO [Formerly UM8473/ id'ed in ses. 427] ELVIN formerly UM1461 KOSIC aka DINO, Medin
Body:
DINO to ELVIR (as per session # 10661/10731/10733)
[Conversation in Albanian language in Italic]
ELVIR: Hey where have u been man?
DINO: Oh God , where have u been?
ELVIR: I am upset with you. ( Laughs)
DINO: Why? ( Laughs)
ELVIR: God forbid if I need your help, I know not to call you.
DINO: Yeah that's right.
[Voices overlapping]
ELVIR: If I'm in a shooting in Canarsie, Brooklyn, don't call Dini.
DINO: Oh god what we did last night.
ELVIR: Yeah
DINO: Oh mother, what a pussy I fucked last night at [Unintelligible] .
ELVIR: [Laughs]
DINO: Oh god, bro
ELVIR: Where are u now? Are u coming to the wedding?
DINO: Yeah, Yeah, I am getting some calls right now.
ELVIR: You come with me and Vali or u come by yourself?
DINO: Why you, is Val,.... is Val going with [Unintelligible] too?
ELVIR: Yeah.
DINO: I assume so. Is there place for us or no?
ELVIR: Yeah, but he is leaving at 5:15 he told me.
DINO: He is leaving at 5:15????
ELVIR: Yeah.
DINO: Oh man, Okay let me call him.
ELVIR: Why? Call him please. You sound like you are at the mall or something. You're
outside.
DINO: I am on Morrisman [PH] ave I am just paying for my shit. I am going home,
taking a shower and...
ELVIR: Call him...
[Voices Overlap]
DINO: He can wait an extra 15 minutes.
ELVIR: Alright. Let me know if he changes the time.
DINO: Bye.
SB: MA.
